      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (NIH, wall shear stress distribution, scalar stress exposure) directly linked to hemolysis risk for CPB Class II devices per FDA guidance.",
      "rationale": "The selected QoIs — NIH, volume-averaged scalar stress, and high-shear-exposure residence time — are the metrics cited in FDA's 2017 guidance for blood-contacting device hemolysis assessment, confirming relevance to the intended decision."
